@Austin Murphy I work for a non profit for seniors that deals with just that, and have been doing it for over 15 years now, and while we get state, and federal funding it does not cover all of our budget needs, and private funding helps but does not always cover it either. In the small town I live in my main office is 35+ minutes away, and the average distance one way to a bigger town is 30+ minutes. running buses several times a days like that gets very very expensive when you factor in the cost of fuel, paying a driver who has to have a CDL every year with a physical, the cost of the buses themselves along with their maintenance.  I'm lucky I get a single bus to pickup some of my clients, and bring them to and from my site, and we have gone through drivers like crap through a goose in the past few years simply because being a non profit we can't pay enough, to get a lot of things done around my site at work I have to pay for it out of pocket. If you don't believe me here is the website of the company I work for. Also to be known if there is a single topic this channel has covered I'm passionate about more than anything then this is it. 
https://www.aikensenior.org/
edit: it should be know that most meals on wheels is volunteer work, and we have enough trouble trying to find volunteers at times to deliver our meal routes, so again with the need of having a CDL, and physical every year, then CPR classes,  plus the time of the person, so good luck in finding someone to do it as volunteer work for a bus route.

